# GRID Layer Model

Read `docs/GRID_LAYER_MODEL.md` before any Studio CMS or content architecture work.

## Mandate

- **Wenige Spiele, maximale Skalierung** вҖ” not a Loquiz-style multi-partner platform
- Content = **modular layers** (1=geo, 2=mission, 3=bonus/roles), freely combinable
- **Fixed engine** (Alpha/Beta/Gamma FSM) + variable JSON snapshots

## Before building a Studio feature

Run the checklist in `lib/cms/layer-model.ts` вҶ’ `LAYER_FEATURE_CHECKLIST`.

If the feature does not serve Layer 1 city scaling, Layer 2 global mission, Layer 3 roles/triggers, or runtime switches (indoor, pulse, language) вҖ” **do not build it**.

## Layer mapping

| Layer | Studio field | Runtime |
|-------|--------------|---------|
| 1 Geo | `studio_tasks.layer=1`, `city_slug`, GPS overrides | `local_waypoints` |
| 2 Mission | `studio_tasks.layer=2` | `global_levels` |
| 3 Bonus | `studio_tasks.layer=3`, `role_assignment`, `logic_rules` | triggers + roles |

## Game profiles

Presets in `LAYER_GAME_PRESETS`: full (1+2+3), city_explorer, mission (2+3), micro_pulse (3 only).

`studio_games.active_layers` + `runtime_profiles` define what runs; `content_mode` on events switches outdoorвҶ”indoor.

## Do not prioritize

- Loquiz clone features (Rogain/Open/Match as primary UX) unless runtime engine supports them
- Generic task library features without layer assignment
- Partner self-service game builder
- Checkout/commerce in GRID

## Key paths

- Layer model: `lib/cms/layer-model.ts`
- Docs: `docs/GRID_LAYER_MODEL.md`
- Layer profile UI: `components/cms/games/game-layer-profile-panel.tsx`
